    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Bank, Southampton,</hi></placeName>
                    <date>May 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> <hi rend="print">18</hi>81</date>
                    <salute>My dear Father,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Things are very high for buyers now.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I should think the following were quite safe</p>
<p>Dutch Government 4 per cents they pay at present price about 3<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></formula> per cent, or Dutch Indian Ry Obligations (ie Railways in Java) guaranteed by Dutch government 4<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></formula> till 1907 these pay about 4<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></formula> per cent at present price; also I could name 2 or 3 first Mortgage Bonds in American Rys which will pay about 4<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></formula> to 4<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></formula> per cent.</p>
<p>If you do not care for any of these, perhaps it would be best to leave the American B<hi rend="superscript">ds</hi>. till they are paid off when things may be cheaper.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
                    <p>Sara is very brisk, &amp; I am going on well.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> | Your affect son | W. E Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. Also Danish Govern<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Bonds pay about 4<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></formula> per cent</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13144.xml">letter to W. E. Darwin, 4 May [1881]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In the event, CD left $14,000  (about £3000) invested in United States Funded Loan shares (CD’s Investment book (Down House MS)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1240.xml">Sara Darwin</ref> was William’s wife. On William’s health, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13144.xml">letter to W. E. Darwin, 4 May [1881]</ref> and n. 1.</note>   
        </div>
    
